main event: Five self-luminous objects were observed over a period of 13 hours in Brunswick, Maine on September 3, 1966.
interesting points: The objects appeared star-like with reddish and bluish colors.
The objects did not distort or move, but one witness said they seemed to change size, appearing and disappearing.
Looking through binoculars only made the objects appear larger, but no further details could be determined.
The sightings were consistent with that of an astro(S/P).
The report includes a response letter from the U.S. Air Force stating that the information provided was insufficient for evaluation.
